  "response_text": "An adult man stands in a bright living room, holding and folding a soft grey item, possibly laundry. He has short dark curly hair, a goatee, and wears a light grey sweater with grey pants. Around him are a blue sofa with patterned and yellow pillows, houseplants, framed wall art, shelves, and a staircase with a gallery wall, giving the room a warm family-home feel.\n\nA young girl appears in another sunlit area of the home, near a glass-paned door and children’s storage shelves. She has dark hair in two braids and wears denim overalls over a striped long-sleeve shirt, a red backpack, bracelets, and white sneakers with colourful accents. She walks through the room dragging a floppy, beige stuffed bunny by one ear or paw. Close to the floor, the plush toy trails along the wood floor beside her shoes, its long ears and soft body brushing the ground as she steps forward.\n\nThe girl lifts the stuffed bunny up to her face and presses it against her mouth and nose, cuddling it closely with both hands. Her eyes peek over the toy. The man is then seen in close-up, looking alert and concerned, as if he has noticed the toy being dragged and then hugged.\n\nBack in the living room, the girl smiles and swings the stuffed bunny forward. The man suddenly lunges across the room in an exaggerated protective pose, arms spread wide and body stretched out horizontally, as if diving to intercept the toy. Large bold white words appear across the scene: “PROTECT MODE.” The phrase stays on screen as he flies past the blue sofa, mouth open and eyes wide, reaching toward the plush bunny at the right side of the room. The moment is playful and dramatic, with the father presented like a superhero reacting to a possible mess or germ risk.\n\nThe man lands back in motion holding the stuffed bunny, while the girl’s arm remains outstretched from the right side of the room. A small line of text appears near the bottom: “Use as directed.” The bunny is dropped into a white laundry basket filled with clothes. Inside the basket, a white bottle with a blue cap is visible among the fabrics. The label identifies it as Lysol Laundry Sanitizer, with “0% Bleach” visible on the front.\n\nThe product is then shown more clearly on a laundry-room counter. A hand holds the white Lysol Laundry Sanitizer bottle upright, label facing forward. The bottle has a rounded shape, a blue cap, and a blue-and-white label with the Lysol logo and “Laundry Sanitizer” prominently displayed. A pale yellow laundry bottle sits blurred in the background.\n\nThe stuffed bunny appears inside a front-loading washing machine, surrounded by light-coloured laundry. The man’s hand closes the round glass door, leaving the bunny visible through the window at the center. The “Use as directed” text remains near the bottom. The man then stands beside the washer with the Lysol Laundry Sanitizer bottle on the counter and the blue cap in his other hand, suggesting he is adding it to the laundry routine.\n\nAfter washing, the girl sits on the blue sofa holding the stuffed bunny close to her chest. She smiles broadly, then squeezes the bunny in a hug, looking happy and comfortable. The living room background remains softly lit, with the staircase and wall art behind her.\n\nThe commercial ends with a product display on a white surface: two bottles of Lysol Laundry Sanitizer with blue caps stand side by side, one larger and one smaller. A red label above the smaller bottle reads “NEW TRIAL SIZE.” Large white text on the right says, “TRY FOR UNDER $5.”",
